-- File: supabase/migrations/00116_import_real_nhd_river_geometry.sql
-- Replace the hand-typed seed LineStrings (~14-40 vertices each, near-
-- straight diagonals — see supabase/seed/rivers.sql) with real NHD HR
-- flowlines from USGS National Map.
--
-- Source: https://prd-tnm.s3.amazonaws.com/StagedProducts/Hydrography/NHD/HU8/Shape/
--   - HUC 11010008 (Current River + Jacks Fork)
--   - HUC 11010011 (Eleven Point River)
--   - HUC 07140102 (Meramec River + Huzzah Creek + Courtois Creek)
--   - HUC 10290110 (Niangua River)
--
-- Pipeline: see scripts/import-nhd-rivers-from-tnm.ts. Per river we
-- filter NHDFlowline by gnis_name + perennial FCode (46006/55800),
-- group into connected components by endpoint adjacency, walk the
-- longest component as a single LineString, and simplify with
-- Douglas-Peucker tolerance 0.0005° (~50 m at MO latitude). Resulting
-- point counts: Meramec 551, Current 632, Niangua 330, Eleven Point 194,
-- Jacks Fork 192, Huzzah 166, Courtois 158 (vs. 14-40 in the old seeds).
--
-- direction_verified is flipped to true because NHD flowlines are
-- canonically downstream-oriented.

